Cameroon Revenue Collection Climbed 20% in First Half of Year

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-09-20T17:47:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/cameroon-revenue-collection-climbed-20-in-first-half-of-year.html
Revenue collection in  Cameroon ,
 Africa â€™s fourth-biggest cocoa producer, increased 20 percent
to 1.12 trillion  CFA francs  ($2.3 billion) in the first half
of the year, Finance Minister Essimi Menye said.  The amount includes a 25 percent increase in oil
earnings, which climbed to 264.3 billion francs, Menye said in
a statement handed to reporters today in Yaounde, the capital.
Non-oil revenue rose 18 percent to 843.3 billion francs, he
said.  Spending increased 11 percent to 1.14 trillion francs on
higher debt servicing, Menye said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
